    "subheading": "One of India’s largest tribes famous for art and nature worship",
    "description": "About the Gond Tribe\n\n• One of the largest tribal communities in India\n• Found across Bastar and southern Chhattisgarh\n• Rich history of art, folklore, and traditions\n\nBeliefs & Lifestyle\n• Worship nature, trees, animals, rivers, and hills\n• Farming and forest collection are main occupations\n• Art is an important part of daily life\n\nArt & Culture\n• Famous for Gond paintings using dots and lines\n• Paintings show animals, trees, and village life\n• Folk songs are sung during festivals and farming\n\nFestivals & Food\n• Madai, Hareli, and Polam Pandum festivals\n• Rice, mahua, forest fruits, and vegetables",
