    "name": "Pahadi Korwa",
    "subheading": "Vulnerable hill tribe living traditionally with deep dependence on forests",
    "description": "About the Pahadi Korwa Tribe\n\n• Classified as a Particularly Vulnerable Tribal Group (PVTG)\n• Lives in hilly and forest areas of northern Chhattisgarh\n• Very limited influence of modern lifestyle\n\nLiving Style\n• Depends heavily on forests for survival\n• Lives in small huts made from mud and bamboo\n• Collects food from deep forest areas\n\nTraditional Skills\n• Archery and hunting skills\n• Making tools from forest materials\n• Strong knowledge of forest paths and nature\n\nFood Sources\n• Mahua collection\n• Roots, tubers, and wild fruits",
